<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-451-073  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 451 073.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 23 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wells American seeks new financing.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenbaum, Daniel J.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wells American Corp. (finance).andO;Ticker:    WAC.andO;Topic:     Computer industryFinancial StabilityManufacturersStrategic Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>WELLS AMERICAN SEEKS NEW FINANCING COLUMBIA, SOUTH CAROLINA, U.S.A., 1990 AUG23 (NB) -- Wells American Corp., a direct-marketing PC clone manufacturerwhich closed its doors suddenly in January, says it will fold completely ifit doesn't find new financing.andM;In reporting its earnings this week, the company said its first quarter saleswere $64,260, down from $2,559,560 for the same period the year before.andO;During the first quarter, the company had a net loss $1,298,300, or 27 centsper share; the year before, the loss was $735,250, or 15 cents per share.andO;Wells American is traded on the American Stock Exchange.andM;Robert K. King, president of the company, said this year's loss included Randamp;Dexpenses for the never-introduced MegaMac Macintosh product line andwrite-downs of about $473,000.andM;In a prepared statement, King said the company will cease operations entirely&quot;unless revenues are restored in the very near future to a level whichprevents further operating losses.&quot;andM;King said the company is negotiating with third parties for an infusion ofcapital.andM;Telephone calls to the company were answered by an answering machine.andM;(Daniel J. Rosenbaum/19900823/Press Contact: Robert K. King, 803-739-1829)</TEXT></DOC>